api.description:
The __ErrorBuilder__ is helpful for the model error handling.

```javascript
// "Builders" is a global variable
var instance = new Builders.ErrorBuilder();
```

methods.description:
Adds the error into the __ErrorBuilder__.

```javascript
var builder = new ErrorBuilder();

// Into the ErrorBuilder you can add the instance of ErrorBuilder.
instance.add(new builders.ErrorBuilder());

instance.add(‘name’, ‘@‘); // Gets the error message according to: instance.onResource(‘name');
// is same as
instance.add(‘name'); // Gets the error message according to: instance.onResource(‘name');

instance.add(‘name', ‘@name-minimum'); // Gets the error message according to: instance.onResource(‘name-minimum');
instance.add(‘name', 'You must enter your name.'); // Skips getting of the value from the resource.
```

